[Student "S"]
{With your 12 point balanced hand you know you are going to play in game. Since you have no interest in looking for a 4-4 Major suit fit you also know that game is going to be 3NT. But you can't actually BID 3NT, because partner would almost surely take you out to a minor suit. Remember, a DIRECT 3NT bid DENIES a stopper in their suit. Since you have East's \S suit stopped, you first bid a lebensohl 2NT.

Partner says 3\C.  

You now complete the picture of your hand by bidding 3NT. (SLOW SHOWS). Partner passes.}

